---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Daily Math Friends · Support">
  <main class="support">
    <header class="page-header">
      <a class="back" href="/">← thehoodiethathoodies</a>
      <h1>Daily Math Friends</h1>
      <p class="kicker">Support</p>
    </header>

    <article>
      <p class="lede">
        Daily Math Friends is a one-puzzle-a-day math app for adults. Same problem
        worldwide each day, a timer that starts the moment you open it, and a
        leaderboard for friends you add by invite code. This page is here to help if
        anything goes sideways.
      </p>

      <h2>Get in touch</h2>
      <p>
        The fastest way to reach us is email. We read every message and reply within a
        couple of days, usually sooner.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="mailto:matthewzhenghi@gmail.com?subject=Daily%20Math%20Friends%20support"
          >matthewzhenghi@gmail.com</a
        >
      </p>
      <p>
        When you write in, it helps to include:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your device and iOS version (e.g. iPhone 14, iOS 18.2).</li>
        <li>The app version, shown at the bottom of the Settings screen.</li>
        <li>The display name or email you signed in with, so we can find your account.</li>
        <li>A short description of what happened and what you expected.</li>
        <li>A screenshot if the issue is visual.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Common questions</h2>

      <h3>I solved today's puzzle but my time didn't save.</h3>
      <p>
        Attempts are graded and saved server-side, so a brief network hiccup can leave
        the app on the result screen without confirming. Pull-to-refresh on the Today
        tab; if your time is missing, email us with the date and we'll restore it.
      </p>

      <h3>The puzzle is the same as my friend's — is that a bug?</h3>
      <p>
        No, that's the design. Everyone in the world gets the same problem each UTC
        day. That's what makes the leaderboard meaningful.
      </p>

      <h3>My friend code didn't work.</h3>
      <p>
        Invite codes are 8 characters from an unambiguous alphabet (no 0/O, 1/I/L). If
        a code doesn't match anyone, double-check the characters with your friend and
        try again. If a request was sent but never appeared, ask them to check the
        Friends tab — incoming requests show up there.
      </p>

      <h3>I'm not getting the daily reminder.</h3>
      <p>
        The reminder is a local iOS notification scheduled by the app — there's no
        server push. If it's not firing:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Check <strong>Settings → Notifications → Daily Math Friends</strong> on your
          device and confirm notifications are allowed.
        </li>
        <li>
          Inside the app, open Settings and toggle the daily reminder off and back on.
          That re-schedules the notification.
        </li>
        <li>If it still doesn't fire, email us and we'll dig in.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>I want to change my display name.</h3>
      <p>Open the app, go to Settings, tap your name, edit, save.</p>

      <h3>How do I sign out or switch accounts?</h3>
      <p>
        Settings → Sign out. The next launch returns you to the sign-in screen, where
        you can use Apple, Google, or email.
      </p>

      <h3>How do I delete my account?</h3>
      <p>
        Email us at
        <a href="mailto:matthewzhenghi@gmail.com?subject=Daily%20Math%20Friends%20account%20deletion"
          >matthewzhenghi@gmail.com</a
        > with the subject "account deletion". We'll confirm and remove your profile,
        all puzzle attempts, and any friendship records within 30 days. This action is
        permanent.
      </p>

      <h3>I think today's answer is wrong.</h3>
      <p>
        It happens. Email us the date and your reasoning — if the answer key is off
        we'll patch it server-side and credit anyone who got the "right" wrong answer.
      </p>

      <h2>Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        For details on what data the app handles and why, see the
        <a href="/privacy/daily-math">Daily Math Friends privacy policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Other apps</h2>
      <p>
        Need help with TripSharing instead? See the
        <a href="/privacy/trip-sharing">TripSharing privacy policy</a>, or email the
        same address — one inbox covers both apps.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .support {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: clamp(2rem, 6vw, 4rem) 0 6rem;
  }

  .page-header {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .back {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }
  .back:hover {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.05;
  }

  .kicker {
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  article {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding-top: 2rem;
  }

  .lede {
    color: var(--text);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--accent);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-top: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  p,
  li {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  p + p {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  ul {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }
  li {
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  strong {
    color: var(--text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }
  a:hover {
    color: var(--accent-dim);
  }
</style>
